<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Another minor idea. Instead of poison-branding at higher levels, maybe PB should bestow POISON_AURA (which was recently implemented in Xband). You become poisonous to the touch. This could also become implemented for monsters. (White Jelly and Poison Ivy come to mind) possibly replacing some attacks. For symbiants, this isn't such a bad deal. You loose a touch-to-poison, but suddenly those packs of Wolves become a lot less annoying...   <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: This can be implemented as a storm effect, but in my opinion it is better to add it in the code together with a cold aura and perhaps even an acid aura. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: You reckon the damage should be level-dependant? (Both Monster and Player/Spell?) 
</p>
<p>
Simon: it should be barely enough to kill breeders of the player's own level (or half his level) in 1 round, and no more, when you stack some of those auras. 
</p>
